<p corresp='TTP1661165P1' xml:id='OTP1661165P1'><rs ref='#S25026074'>Executive Office</rs>,<lb/>
<rs ref='#S51785'>Jackson</rs>, Miss. May 6<add place='above'><hi rend='underline'>th</hi></add>,,1861.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1661165P2' xml:id='OTP1661165P2'>Dear Sir
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1661165P3' xml:id='OTP1661165P3'>The Governor prefers a statement of the case &amp; the facts connected with or pertinent to the main points before granting a <rs ref='#S62927'>pardon</rs> for <rs ref='#S86101'>Hansford Rawley</rs> which you will please send soon &amp; oblige
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1661165P4' xml:id='OTP1661165P4'>Yours Respectfully
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1661165P5' xml:id='OTP1661165P5'><rs ref='#S86102'>J. C. Campbell</rs><lb/>
Private Secty
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1661165P6' xml:id='OTP1661165P6'>Col. <rs ref='#S63218'>G. S. M<add place='above'>c</add>Millan</rs><lb/>
<rs ref='#S63212'>Monticello</rs><lb/>
Miss. 
</p>


